Git is a program that enables us to save data in a file system and often depends on local files .. The files can exist in 3 main cases:
... the data is stored securely in the database
..the file is changed

Some of Git's features:
Execute changes .. hide changes .. rename .. create a new branch .. merge and others ...

log :

1. to list the exhaustive commit history

   $ git log

2. to line only allows for 3 displayed commit

    $git log -n3

3. to shows the full different of each commit

    $git log -p

4.  allows for a specific search for commits by an author whose name includes the string “smith.”

    $git log index.html 

5. to command above will display only those commits 

    including the index.html file.

     $ git log --oneline